## Starting Point

The user reported several urgent hardware/runtime problems:

- B4 audio-only AI agent could start and double-click stop correctly.
- B5 camera/vision AI agent could start, but physical double-click stop stopped
  working after the camera path was used.
- B6 SOS double-click was no longer reliably triggering SOS; single clicks kept
  logging the warning instead.
- B2 visual/camera action repeatedly failed with:
  "Camera __init__ sequence did not complete."
- B2 double-click video recording only created a short 5 second clip and had no
  audio.
- Documentation and voice-note buttons were mostly working, which suggested the
  failure was not a total GPIO/dashboard failure.

The relevant log excerpt showed:

- WebSocket connection worked.
- OpenAI Realtime audio session started and stopped.
- B5 OpenAI vision session attempted to start but camera open failed.
- Physical B6 clicks were being recognized as single clicks instead of a double.
- B2 single photo calls failed with camera initialization errors.
- Voice notes were saved successfully after stale mic blocks were drained.

