## Important Behavioral Summary

After today's work:

- B1 documentation session toggle remains unchanged.
- B2 single photo is still a photo action, but it refuses while video recording
  is active.
- B2 double video is now start/stop video with audio.
- B3 voice note still records through `AudioBridge`, but refuses while B2 video
  is using the mic.
- B4 AI audio can start/stop, but refuses while B2 video is recording.
- B5 AI vision can start/stop and snap, but refuses while B2 video is recording.
- B6 SOS double-click was repaired via button gesture fixes, and it can stop
  active B2 video before arming SOS.

## Remaining Notes

- The final B2 test was performed through the dashboard endpoint. That endpoint
  is the same one called by the GPIO bridge, so the physical B2 double-click
  should follow the same behavior.
- The user should still physically test B2 double-click on the wearable because
  actual button feel and timing are hardware-dependent.
- There is a 300 second safety timeout for video recording. It exists to avoid a
